column1: # These mappings serve to map input from a swedish keyboard layout to a generic
#    Q2 Q  W  E  R  T  Y  U  I  O  P  P2 P3 ret
#    A2 A  S  D  F  G  H  J  K  L  L2 L3 L4
# Z3 Z2 Z  X  C  V  B  N  M  M2 M3 M4 M5
#          S4 S3 S2 space D1 D2 D3
#dead_abovedot is duplicated on M3 and M4
# Additional custom commonname mappings for layout1
# These mappings serve to map input from an Ergodox EZ with the following custom layout:
# Tab  Q    W    E    R    T    F3                  F4   Y    U    I    O    P    Å
# F5   A    S    D    F    G                             H    J    K    L    Ö    Ä
# <    Z    X    C    V    B    F6                  F7   N    M
#                          Back Del  F23       F24  Ret  Space
# to a generic-key name like so:
# Q2   Q    W    E    R    T    T2                  Y2   Y    U    I    O    P    P2
# A2   A    S    D    F    G                             H    J    K    L    L2   L3
# Z2   Z    X    C    V    B    B2                  N2   N    M    M2   M3   M4   M5
# S5   S4   S3   S2   _                                       D1   D2   D3   D4   _
#                          back del  SC4       DC4  ret  space
# when used from Windows set to swedish layout
